language=EN>Fraethir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/26/01 12:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AE spells, large agro radius since patch this AM</span><hr size=1> AE spells have always had Z-axis problems. And LDogs is underneath Udogs (lord knows I&quot;ve sat in upper dogs watching spells from folks below killing something I wanted to attack). If they were under UDogs and cast the wrong spell, they could have pulled from overhead and had them path down picking more up.<br>
<br>
AoE spells can be dangerous, but from what I've seen aggro radius is a function of where you are in relation to the mob, the mob itself, and your level. Adding in ranged AoE (like a Pillar), you add the risk of catching someone to the side, overhead, or under, in many situations but the first three things are the key from what I've seen.<br>
<br>
Twiceborn Fraethir<br>
Sutekh<br>
Kephra<br>
